{"TopicId":102277,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8] PersistentRotation 1.8.6","CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-19T21:24:41Z","PageNum":19,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Conventia","CreatedById":143229,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T01:03:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... the issue seems to start here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\n[LOG 02:38:24.733] Packing Harrier 1 for orbit\n[LOG 02:38:41.422] 9/12/2016 2:38:41 AM,KerbalAlarmClock,Reducing Warp-Transition\n[LOG 02:38:42.523] Unpacking Harrier 1\n[ERR 02:38:42.805] Infinity or NaN floating point numbers appear when calculating the transform matrix for a Collider. Scene hierarchy path \u0022HECS2.ProbeCore (Harrier 1)/model/VenStockRevamp/Squad/Parts/Command/ProbeCores/HECS2(Clone)/Hecs2Tops/Collider\u0022\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy assumption being that there is a bad interaction between \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E stopping warp and PR applying the appropriate \u0027rotation\u0027 to the vessel after warp is over? PR wouldn\u0027t have to have an exception for it to be \u0027at fault\u0027. All the exceptions below this are probably due to the bad unpack here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI appreciate you taking the time to look at it. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T06:09:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222753229\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473728625\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143229\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Conventia\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Conventia said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm... the issue seems to start here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\n\n[LOG 02:38:24.733] Packing Harrier 1 for orbit\n[LOG 02:38:41.422] 9/12/2016 2:38:41 AM,KerbalAlarmClock,Reducing Warp-Transition\n[LOG 02:38:42.523] Unpacking Harrier 1\n[ERR 02:38:42.805] Infinity or NaN floating point numbers appear when calculating the transform matrix for a Collider. Scene hierarchy path \u0022HECS2.ProbeCore (Harrier 1)/model/VenStockRevamp/Squad/Parts/Command/ProbeCores/HECS2(Clone)/Hecs2Tops/Collider\u0022\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy assumption being that there is a bad interaction between \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E stopping warp and PR applying the appropriate \u0027rotation\u0027 to the vessel after warp is over? PR wouldn\u0027t have to have an exception for it to be \u0027at fault\u0027. All the exceptions below this are probably due to the bad unpack here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI appreciate you taking the time to look at it. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, it could be. But PR only applies some force and / or sets the rotation of the vessel when unpacking. If something goes wrong, it tells you. I\u0027d first knock at a couple of other devs than on the one whose mod does not throw any errors at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, maybe there is some incompatibility between my mod and one of the others, but it\u0027s them throwing the exceptions, so it\u0027s something I can\u0027t do anything about.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-14T09:42:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExperimental 1.2 compatibility to be tested by you guys!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun rotating \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scorp1579","CreatedById":29793,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-15T23:32:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222755783\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473846121\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 14/09/2016 at 10:42 AM, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExperimental 1.2 compatibility to be tested by you guys!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun rotating \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow amazing work!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Marcelo Silveira","CreatedById":98059,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T00:00:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nheheheheheheh \u0022Have fun rotating\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NubNibble","CreatedById":139531,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-23T02:09:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe icon for the mod doesnt show up for me on the right side toolbar, nor in the 000 toolbar. Positive I installed correctly though. Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lazy8","CreatedById":123610,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-23T05:16:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222770039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474596568\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139531\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NubNibble\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, NubNibble said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe icon for the mod doesnt show up for me on the right side toolbar, nor in the 000 toolbar. Positive I installed correctly though. Any ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMine goes a little farther than that, not only do I not get the icons to show but the mod isn\u0027t working at all or doesn\u0027t load with the latest release. Reverting back to previous solves the issue. Something changed and isn\u0027t working for me. I run this in a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E modded game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"inigma","CreatedById":69310,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-23T05:44:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222755783\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473846121\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/14/2016 at 3:42 AM, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExperimental 1.2 compatibility to be tested by you guys!\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/MarkusA380/PersistentRotation/archive/Development.zip\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun rotating \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot loading icons nor is persistent rotation working\u00A0at all here either. Tell us what you need to troubleshoot!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-23T06:01:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you all have the newest version of KSP 1.2-pre? 1.1.3 is not supported anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-23T13:53:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222770336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474610484\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you all have the newest version of KSP 1.2-pre? 1.1.3 is not supported anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust uninstalled the latest version and download and install the\u00A01.1.3 manually here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-23T13:55:15Z\u0022 title=\u002209/23/2016 01:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 23, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DrLicor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Friedrich Nietzsche","CreatedById":106208,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T16:18:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222770336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474610484\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MarkusA380\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 23.9.2016 at 8:01 AM, MarkusA380 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you all have the newest version of KSP 1.2-pre? 1.1.3 is not supported anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly not supported anyomore. Or not working anymore?\u00A0The latter would be quite annonying. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECkan\u003C/abbr\u003E replaced persistent rotation already with 1.8 in my installation and I won\u0027t be changing to 1.2 soon, because many other mods will have to be updated. So it would be nice to have a working and up to date\u00A0persistant rotation mod in the mean time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome mod btw, keep up the good work\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dtrauma","CreatedById":109053,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T20:19:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E thinks 1.8.1 is for KSP 1.1.3, which is bad for both people with 1.2 and 1.1.3 :).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Olympic1","CreatedById":79730,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-24T21:49:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222772686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474748398\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022109053\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dtrauma\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, dtrauma said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E thinks 1.8.1 is for KSP 1.1.3, which is bad for both people with 1.2 and 1.1.3 :).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E has some issues if you have two different buildID\u0027s. If the one is 1.1.3 and other 1.2, it will choose the 1.1.3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: This will be fixed with the next \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E release, for now you can get around this issue by deleting the 1.1.3 buildID.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-25T10:06:52Z\u0022 title=\u002209/25/2016 10:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Olympic1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eupdate\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodger","CreatedById":153575,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T14:02:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if this is a bug or a feature, but I seem to be getting a bit of drift in KSP 1.2pre 1532 and PR 1.8.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/ZXhPW\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/ZXhPW\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T14:14:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222773555\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474812142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153575\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rodger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Rodger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if this is a bug or a feature, but I seem to be getting a bit of drift in KSP 1.2pre 1532 and PR 1.8.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/ZXhPW\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/ZXhPW\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen turning \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and MechJeb off the vessel indeed falls back into Momentum Mode. Even when there is no visible momentum to the eye, there will always be a slight amount of it, so in Momentum Mode you will experience a drift anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodger","CreatedById":153575,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T14:21:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh yes, I didn\u0027t notice the switch to momentum mode. And the reason I\u0027d tested it with no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is I just forgot that you needed to set \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold, not to some \u0027advanced\u0027 marker lol\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s definitely working as intended though, thanks for the update!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso an idea for a new minor feature - an option to have it default to on/dynamic?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-25T14:28:38Z\u0022 title=\u002209/25/2016 02:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Rodger\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MarkusA380","CreatedById":45759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T14:32:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222773584\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474813308\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153575\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rodger\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Rodger said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh yes, I didn\u0027t notice the switch to momentum mode. And the reason I\u0027d tested it with no \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E is I just forgot that you needed to set \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to hold, not to some \u0027advanced\u0027 marker lol\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s definitely working as intended though, thanks for the update!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso an idea for a new minor feature - an option to have it default to on/dynamic?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGo into the config window \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodger","CreatedById":153575,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T14:35:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh so THAT\u0027S what \u0027default reference body means! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E derp lol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"inigma","CreatedById":69310,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-25T15:20:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic